==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hydroquinone
<hw>Hy`dro*qui"none</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hydro-</ets>, 2 + <ets>quinone</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white crystalline substance,
<chform>C6H4(OH)2</chform>, obtained by the reduction of quinone. It is
a diacid phenol, resembling, and metameric with, pyrocatechin and
resorcin. Called also <altname>dihydroxy benzene</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hydrorhiza</ent>⟦br⟧
